{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"62d539c0-dfdb-4141-93ec-afb4f2fd73be","content":"There's no workflow file in this directory. Since there's no existing code to inspect, here's a summary of the changes needed to switch to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. GitHub Actions Workflow Changes\n\n**Remove:**\n- The `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` reference from your `dotnet nuget push` step.\n\n**Add:**\n- `permissions: id-token: write` at the job level (required for OIDC token generation).\n- Use `dotnet nuget push` with `--source` pointing to `nuget.org` — **no `--api-key`**.\n- Add the `setup-dotnet` action's built-in trusted publishing support:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          source-url: https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\n### 2. NuGet.org Configuration\n\nOn **nuget.org**, configure a trusted publisher for your package:\n\n1. Go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted Publishers**.\n2. Add a new GitHub Actions policy specifying:\n   - **Repository owner** and **name**\n   - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch**, **tag**, or **environment**.\n\n### 3. Clean Up\n\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository's **Settings → Secrets** once you've verified the OIDC flow works.\n\n---\n\n**Key benefit:** No more long-lived secrets — authentication is scoped per-workflow-run via short-lived OIDC tokens.\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"70071bd6-df0c-46df-8658-703ba339afc7","outputTokens":505,"requestId":"041B:1EBB02:462FFC:51FAA2:69F0050A"},"id":"b4d77934-7a1c-4